question:
District category contains Shopping District, Senior Living Community, and Wall Street.
Supermarkets category contains Food Lion, Thrive Market, and Mitsuwa Marketplace.
Product category contains Danish Pastries, Canned Sauces, and Protein Shakes.
The number of each Senior Living Community 's Thrive Market equals 14.
The number of each Shopping District 's Mitsuwa Marketplace equals 15 times each Wall Street 's Food Lion.
The number of each Thrive Market 's Danish Pastries equals 10 more than the difference of each Thrive Market 's Canned Sauces and each Shopping District 's Food Lion.
The number of each Thrive Market 's Canned Sauces equals 11 times the sum of each Shopping District 's Food Lion and each Senior Living Community 's Thrive Market.
The number of each Thrive Market 's Protein Shakes equals the sum of each Senior Living Community 's Thrive Market, each Thrive Market 's Canned Sauces, and each Thrive Market 's Danish Pastries.
The number of each Wall Street 's Thrive Market equals 16.
The number of each Mitsuwa Marketplace 's Danish Pastries equals 11 times each Food Lion 's Canned Sauces.
The number of each Shopping District 's Food Lion equals 22 more than each Senior Living Community 's Thrive Market.
The number of each Senior Living Community 's Mitsuwa Marketplace equals 14.
The number of each Food Lion 's Canned Sauces equals 15.
The number of each Food Lion 's Danish Pastries equals the difference of each Food Lion 's Canned Sauces and each Shopping District 's Food Lion.
The number of each Wall Street 's Mitsuwa Marketplace equals 15 more than the sum of each Thrive Market 's Canned Sauces, each Food Lion 's Danish Pastries, and each Food Lion 's Protein Shakes.
The number of each Wall Street 's Food Lion equals 14.
The number of each Food Lion 's Protein Shakes equals each Thrive Market 's Canned Sauces.
How many Product does Thrive Market have?
solution:
Define each Senior Living Community 's Thrive Market as r; So r = 14.
Define each Shopping District 's Food Lion as F; So F = 22 + r = 22 + 14 = 13.
Define each Thrive Market 's Canned Sauces as D; q = F + r = 13 + 14 = 4; So D = 11 * q = 11 * 4 = 21.
Define each Thrive Market 's Danish Pastries as b; q = D - F = 21 - 13 = 8; So b = 10 + q = 10 + 8 = 18.
Define each Thrive Market 's Protein Shakes as h; A = r + b = 14 + 18 = 9; So h = D + A = 21 + 9 = 7.
Define each Thrive Market 's Product as I; a = b + D = 18 + 21 = 16; So I = h + a = 7 + 16 = 0.
